{
  "text": "In this paper we make a step in applying the general framework described above. Our main result provides randomized k-server algorithms for a natural class of metric spaces defined on unweighted graphs having bounded growth-rate, including d-dimensional grids. The growth-rate (see [CITATION_1] ) of an unweighted graph M is \u03c1 = max{log |B(x, r)|/ log r; x \u2208 M, r \u2265 2}. Such metric spaces can be probabilistically approximated by HSTs with some special properties that enable us to get better algorithms. The competitive ratio we obtain for the class of growth-rate \u03c1 is \u2206",
  "citation_candidates": [
